<subSubSection id="F5B8A4FFDE42FFBFFF35FE0EFEC3FD50" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BD1DF774DE42FFBFFF35FE0EFEC3FD50" blockId="4.[189,794,393,641]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis id="8FD62B66DE42FFBFFF35FE0EFE9BFE70" bold="true" box="[189,286,393,417]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Remarks</emphasis>
: As a consequence of the new combination here established, the 
<collectingCountry id="C5B5B7E4DE42FFBFFEE6FE2DFE7AFE10" box="[366,511,425,449]" name="New Zealand" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
species 
<taxonomicName id="7AA28CF7DE42FFBFFDD6FE2EFEC2FE30" authority="PARENT, 1933" authorityName="PARENT" authorityYear="1933" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinus">
<emphasis id="8FD62B66DE42FFBFFDD6FE2EFC9FFE10" box="[606,794,425,449]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">Chrysotus vicinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D9338A85DE42FFBFFF35FE4EFEC2FE30" author="PARENT, O." box="[189,327,457,481]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" pagination="325 - 441" refId="ref6007" refString="PARENT, O. 1933: Etude monographique sur les Dipteres Dolichopodides de Nouvelle-Zelande. - Annales de la Societe scientifique de Bruxelles (B) 53: 325 - 441, 205 figs." type="book chapter" year="1933">PARENT,1933</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
becomes a junior secondary homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="7AA28CF7DE42FFBFFF53FE6EFE31FDD0" authority="(BECKER)" baseAuthorityName="BECKER" box="[219,436,489,513]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinus">
<emphasis id="8FD62B66DE42FFBFFF53FE6EFEC6FDD0" box="[219,323,489,513]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">C. vicinus</emphasis>
(BECKER)
</taxonomicName>
. As such, the replacement name 
<taxonomicName id="7AA28CF7DE42FFBFFF35FD8EFDB1FDF0" authority="CAPELLARI &amp; AMORIM" authorityName="CAPELLARI &amp; AMORIM" authorityYear="2014" box="[189,564,521,545]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kallweiti" status="nom. n.">
<emphasis id="8FD62B66DE42FFBFFF35FD8EFEB7FDF0" box="[189,306,521,545]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">C. kallweiti</emphasis>
CAPELLARI &amp; AMORIM
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="94E5961DDE42FFBFFDCAFD8DFD10FDF0" box="[578,661,522,545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="379">nom. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is proposed for PARENT’s species. The species is named after Dr. UWE KALLWEIT, who supported the first author during a visit to the SNSD.
</paragraph>
